04/07/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Washington will provide $3m in assistance to Macedonia under the solidarity fund of the coalition for Iraq and Afghanistan, according to a report Friday (1 July) by A1 TV, which cited a statement from the US Embassy in Skopje. The funds are to be used to modernise army equipment and enhance military information technology. 
In other news, Italian Army Chief Giampaolo di Paola kicks off a two-day visit to Macedonia on Monday. Bilateral co-operation and Euro-Atlantic integration are expected to dominate the agenda.
Also Monday, Macedonian Justice Minister Meri Mladenovska-Gjorgievska goes before The Hague tribunal to officially present government guarantees issued on behalf of former Interior Minister Ljube Boskovski and former security official Johan Tarculovski. Skopje is seeking their release on bail, allowing them to return to Macedonia until their trial begins. The two were indicted for war crimes stemming from the 2001 interethnic conflict in Macedonia. (Makfax, A1 TV - 04/07/05; A1 TV - 01/07/05)
